HEADWORD: Insole
<hw>In"sole`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The inside sole of a
boot or shoe; also, a loose, thin strip of leather, felt, etc., placed
inside the shoe for warmth or ease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insolence</ent>⟦br⟧
